# Opt-in remote state backend (Azure Blob Storage) for the l1/azure root.
#
# Local state (terraform.tfstate in this directory) is the DEFAULT. Nothing in
# this repo requires remote state, and `terraform init` works without this file.
#
# How to opt in:
#   1. Use a PRE-EXISTING storage account + container (create them out-of-band
#      with blob versioning enabled; do not let Terraform create its own state
#      storage).
#   2. cp backend.tf.example backend.tf    # then edit the values below
#   3. terraform init -migrate-state       # copies local state into the blob
#   4. Commit backend.tf so every operator points at the same state.
#
# WARNING: ALL operators of a deployment must switch together. Mixing local and
# remote state against the same infrastructure guarantees drift and clobbering.
#
# The azurerm backend provides state locking natively via blob leases.
# Each terraform root must use a DISTINCT `key`. This root: l1/azure.
#
# terraform {
#   backend "azurerm" {
#     resource_group_name  = "REPLACE-ME-rg"
#     storage_account_name = "REPLACEMESTATESA"
#     container_name       = "tfstate"
#     key                  = "avalanche-deploy/l1/azure/terraform.tfstate"
#   }
# }
